      </div>
      
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3 class="card-title">Best Indicators for Gold</h3>
        
        <p><strong>1. RSI (Relative Strength Index)</strong><br />
        Gold tends to reverse at extreme RSI readings. Below 30 = oversold bounce incoming. Above 70 = overbought correction likely.</p>
        
        <p><strong>2. Moving Averages</strong><br />
        The 50-day and 200-day MAs are crucial. Golden cross (50 above 200) signals bull market. Death cross signals bear market.</p>
        
        <p><strong>3. Bollinger Bands</strong><br />
        Gold often tags the upper/lower bands before reversing. Squeeze patterns (bands narrowing) precede big moves.</p>
        
        <div class="insight-box">
          <p>‚ö° <strong>Quick Win:</strong> Combine RSI divergence with support/resistance for 70%+ win rate setups.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

